    "body": "> If you use the latest version of Vue InstantSearch, you can fix this by:\r\n> \r\n> 1. use `<ais-instantsearch :future=\"{ preserveSharedStateOnUnmount: true }\">`\r\n> 2. add a static (can be non-rendering, hidden) widget of the type that is conditionally rendered\r\n> \r\n> I'll close this issue now, but the guide on https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/building-search-ui/widgets/show-and-hide-widgets/react/ should be recreated for Vue (it behaves the same)\r\n\r\nidk why this is not working for me btw i'm using nuxt/@algolia last version\r\n",
